result.execSummary:
The defendant Amanda M. West was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons.

Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   Defendant to complete a Domestic Abuse Alternatives Program or Anger Management Program together with any follow through counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

records.addlTxt: 11:48 am cases called-13CM61, 14CF77 & 14CM224. Defendant Amanda M. West in court with attorney Ryan S. Ulrich.  Steven P. Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on record. Amend Count 1 of 14CF77 to Obstructing in violation of 946.41(1).  Court questions defendant regarding Deferred Sentencing agreement-material violation has occurred, defendant concurs.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest to Count 1 of 14CF77 & No Contest to Count 2 of 14CM224. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses Count 2 of 14CF77 & Count 1 of 14CM224. No statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to-EACH CASE: SWD and places the defendant on probation for a period of 2 years. If revoked, 1 day credit. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through, Maintain Absolute Sobriety, No Bars, Not to ingest any impairing substances without a valid prescription from a physician. Terms of Agent, Complete DAAP or Anger Management, Not to possess any dangerous weapons. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. (No DNA surcharge on 13CM61). Bond to be applied. Appeal Rights Given.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 3, 2014 at 11:45 am.
Status conference on July 25, 2014 at 02:45 pm.
